title: Missing labeled data

labels.name: duplicate
labels.description: This issue or pull request already exists

body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

I have labelled my frames and I have saved the labels, but the folder with the labels doesn't seem to have the labeled data. The .h5 file is missing and there is no labeled data. 
I have got the CSV file in the folder with the coordinates labeled perfectly. I can thus also not train the neural network. 

I have tried multiple things - pip uninstall tables followed by pip install tables; conda uninstall pytables followed by conda install tables. However, I cannot seem to overcome this error. 

I also thought of separately converting the CSV file to the .h5 file using tables myself, but the same import error in tables persists in the DLC ipython terminal. 

I would be highly obliged if you could help me overcome this error. 

### Operating System

Windows 11

### DeepLabCut version

dlc version 2.2.0.5

### DeepLabCut mode

single animal

### Device type

gpu RTX 3060

### Steps To Reproduce
